subject: p16957952
Findings: Increased interstitial markings seen throughout the lungs, not significantly changed since prior. There is no focal consolidation nor effusion. There is moderate cardiac enlargement and tortuosity of the descending thoracic aorta. Compression deformity of several upper lumbar vertebral bodies are again noted. No acute osseous abnormalities.
Impression: Cardiomegaly with pulmonary vascular congestion but no overt edema.
